Old Bear Priest: Return to us once you've completed your Rite of Passage.
Old Bear Priest: ...*growl*...RARGH!!
Teenage Bear: ...*growl*...*growl*...!
Crushfang: Dagger...
Crushfang: ...Good luck...
Old Bear Priest: Worried about Dagger?
Crushfang: A bit.
Old Bear Priest: Hahaha, no need to worry, that cub is almost a carbon copy of the younger Crushfang.
Old Bear Priest: In fact, he may be more mature now than you were back then.
Crushfang: More mature than me? Nonsense!
Old Bear Priest: Hahaha, Crushfang, it seems like age has taken a toll on your memory.
Crushfang: My memory is just fine!
Old Bear Priest: Heh. Alright, alright. Have some wine, don't worry about Dagger.
Razorclaw: Hey, done wandering around?
Crushfang: Ra-Razorclaw...?
Razorclaw: Everybody else is on their way, better get going before it is too late.
Crushfang: What the... did everyone already set out?
Razorclaw: Unlucky draw. We ended up being the last group to start.
Crushfang: What are we waiting for then?
Crushfang: There might not be any good fate weapons left!
Crushfang: These monsters are so weak! Remember those Helmetal Pinchers the elders always talked about?
Crushfang: Let's go find one and fight it.
Razorclaw: Don't waste time. Last to start, first to finish. Isn't that our goal?
Crushfang: Pffftt~ You wimp! I'll go by myself, it's probably no big deal anyway.

Crushfang: Smaller than I thought. The elders must have been exaggerating. 
...Is it already dead? No reaction at all.
Crushfang: Okay, help!! I can't take this thing!
Razorclaw: Haha, didn't you say it would be no big deal?
Crushfang: Quit it, alright? It's stronger than I thought!
? ? ?: Some bears are calling for help.
? ? ?: I heard. Let's go check it out!

Razorclaw: Ah, someone's coming... 
Alright, let's get this over with!
Crushfang: Yeah, you better run! Next time, you're dead!
Razorclaw: Now he acts all tough...
Crushfang: Did I fall asleep?
Old Bear Priest: Yes, for quite a while, too.
Crushfang: ...I had a dream about my Rite of Passage with Razorclaw.
Crushfang: I have forgotten that I was once a young and reckless bear.
Old Bear Priest: Who wasn't? One must be reckless before learning to grow.
Crushfang: ......
Old Bear Priest: Try letting go, the kid is smart.
Old Bear Priest: If you let him lose on his own, he'll come to understand your words.
Old Bear Priest: Ah, the first group to clear the Rite of Passage is here. Not bad. Not bad, indeed. You're the fastest group in recent years.
Crushfang: Dagger, I congratulate you in place of your father, Razorclaw.
Crushfang: As a grown bear, I will no longer restrict you. You are now responsible for your own actions.
Dagger: Hmph.
